Key Match Events: Jon Dagur Thorsteinsson scored the only goal of the match in the 12th minute, giving Iceland a 1-0 victory over England.
England had 68.1% possession but only managed one shot on goal compared to Iceland's four.
Iceland received three yellow cards while England received none.
Post-Match Reflections: England's loss to Iceland was a surprising and disappointing result in their final warm-up match before Euro 2024.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was held at Wembley Stadium with an attendance of 81,410.
The referee for the match was Davide Massa.
